parameters:
Male Researcher: I'm conducting research on heating alcohol
and collecting the vapor... How about having a drink if it
goes well?

Cors the Wanderer: It's scary how the adventurer guild's
information network always knows where I am.

Cors the Wanderer: I can imagine, but shall I hear your
business?

Clea: Do you know the whereabouts of Celis from the
Adventurer's Guild?

Clea: There's no way Cors-san hasn't heard about the
negotiations in the Mucos region.
Cors the Wanderer: That's just an exaggeration, you know.

Cors the Wanderer: Speaking of what I know... everyone's
actions are being scrutinized in the Mucos region.

Cors the Wanderer: Mucos is a conflict zone with various
factions vying for power. It's even escalated to a struggle
between the Queen's faction and the Prince's faction, you
know.

Cors the Wanderer: Haha, if you were threatened, there's no
helping it. The majority of the organization's forces
support the Queen's faction, you see.

Cors the Wanderer: After all, some of the Prince's faction
are talking about turning this Mucos into a sea of fire, you
know.

Cors the Wanderer: As for her whereabouts, I heard that the
abandoned cemetery organization drove their enemies there.
Clea: Why are you telling me so honestly?

Cors the Wanderer: It's because you all sided with the
Prince's faction, you see. As a gambler, my instincts tell
me that you all will win.

Cors the Wanderer: As an information provider who won't get
caught up in the war in Mucos, I can receive some benefits
from the Prince.

Cors the Wanderer: I'm looking forward to everyone's
activities. The organization is not united, after all. Well
then, I'll take my leave.

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Mucos Region / Abandoned
Cemetery\c[0]
